cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with computer vision applications and specifically focuses on attribute classification of humans, which falls under the domain of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method that involves machine learning solutions, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper introduces a loss function to handle class imbalance, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of weak supervision, which could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
